description:
Message.sender_id is typed as String but the spec defines exactly two cases: the magic literal "self" (owner-composed) and a ChatContact.id. Every UI crate must string-compare against "self" in their render logic.

Design:
  #[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Serialize, Deserialize)]
  #[serde(untagged)]
  pub enum SenderId {
      #[serde(rename = "self")]
      SelfComposed,
      Contact(Id),
  }

  impl SenderId {
      pub fn is_self(&self) -> bool { matches!(self, SenderId::SelfComposed) }
      pub fn contact_id(&self) -> Option<&Id> { ... }
  }

Change Message.sender_id: String to Message.sender_id: SenderId.

Note: serde untagged with a rename is tricky — verify that #[serde(rename = "self")] on a unit variant of an untagged enum produces the correct wire format. May need a custom Deserialize impl.

Tests: deserialize sender_id "self" to SenderId::SelfComposed; deserialize a ULID string to SenderId::Contact(Id); assert round-trip serialization.
